chunk_content: DATIM users will still see these modalities on the data entry screen but will no longer be able to enter data directly into the modalities. Once data are entered for the parent indicator, they will be copied into the relevant data entry form for the corresponding HTS modality. For further details, see the diagram below and review the HTS_TST reference sheet. 21 Figure 9: Auto-Population of HTS_TST From Associated Indicators Updated for MER v2.7 O V E R V I E W AUTO-SUM NUMERATORS AND DENOMINATORS: To reinforce data quality and reduce data entry, PEPFAR began auto-summing the top-level numerators and denominators for most indicators in FY 2019. For example, the age/sex disaggregations for TX_CURR is summed to obtain the total numerator for TX_CURR. Implementing partners do not need to enter both a numerator and the age/sex disaggregations into DATIM as entering the age/sex disaggregations will auto-sum the numerator.
